cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with action classification in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm that uses machine learning techniques such as logistic regression with L2 regularization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of Histogram of Oriented Gradient (HOG3D) feature and the comparison with other state-of-the-art algorithms indicate that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
